---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../config/site";

const title = `About | ${SITE.name}`;
const description =
  "About CloudCostKit: fast, practical cloud cost and capacity calculators with transparent assumptions and validation workflows.";
const [emailUser, emailDomain] = SITE.email.split("@");
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/about">
  <section class="card hero">
    <h1>About {SITE.name}</h1>
    <p>Practical calculators for cloud planning: egress, logs, storage, Kubernetes, and break-even analysis.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Principles</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Transparent assumptions: each tool defines what is included and excluded.</li>
      <li>Utility first: focus on measurable drivers and decision-ready outputs.</li>
      <li>Privacy-friendly: calculators run in your browser.</li>
      <li>Validation-oriented: every estimate should map to real billing or metrics data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">What this site is for</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li><strong>Budgeting</strong>: get a directional monthly estimate quickly.</li>
      <li><strong>Comparisons</strong>: compare workload shapes, tiers, and architecture options.</li>
      <li><strong>Right-sizing</strong>: convert requirements into billable units.</li>
      <li><strong>Validation</strong>: reconcile estimates against billing exports and metrics.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">How we maintain quality</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Each page must include unique decision guidance and validation steps.</li>
      <li>Similar topics are split by intent so pages are not template duplicates.</li>
      <li>High-traffic pages are refreshed first when pricing patterns drift.</li>
      <li>Calculator and guide pages are maintained together for better user outcomes.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">How to get accurate estimates</h2>
    <ol class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Start with measurable drivers (requests/month, GB/month, hours, GB-month).</li>
      <li>Use effective rates first to get directionality.</li>
      <li>Add boundaries and multipliers (retries, fan-out, cache hit rate).</li>
      <li>Validate against a real week of data and update assumptions.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">
      See <a href="/methodology/">Methodology</a> and the <a href="/guides/cloud-cost-estimation-checklist/">estimation checklist</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">Data and pricing sources</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:0">
      Calculators accept your own pricing because provider rates vary by region, tiering, discounts, and product
      options. For official reference, use provider pricing pages and then validate against your billing exports.
    </p>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>
        AWS:{" "}
        <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/pricing/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">
          aws.amazon.com/pricing
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        Azure:{" "}
        <a href="https://azure.microsoft.com/pricing/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">
          azure.microsoft.com/pricing
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        Google Cloud:{" "}
        <a href="https://cloud.google.com/pricing" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">
          cloud.google.com/pricing
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">Limitations</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Tools are simplified planning models; production bills can differ due to pricing rules.</li>
      <li>Incidents can shift cost drivers quickly (retries, bot spikes, backfills).</li>
      <li>Provider documentation remains the source of truth for procurement decisions.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">Contact</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:0">
      Feedback and suggestions:{" "}
      <a href="#" data-email-user={emailUser} data-email-domain={emailDomain}>
        Email us
      </a>
      <noscript>
        {" "}
        ({emailUser} [at] {emailDomain})
      </noscript>
      .
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
